Subject: [PATCH 27/43] serial: linflexuart: add DEBUG_UART_LINFLEXUART

Add DEBUG_UART_LINFLEXUART to Kconfig.

Issue: ALB-8504

Upstream-Status: Pending 

Signed-off-by: Radu Pirea (NXP OSS) <radu-nicolae.pirea@oss.nxp.com>
Signed-off-by: Zhantao Tang <zhantao.tang@windriver.com>
---
 drivers/serial/Kconfig | 7 +++++++
 1 file changed, 7 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/serial/Kconfig b/drivers/serial/Kconfig
index 90e3983170..0249abc516 100644
--- a/drivers/serial/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/serial/Kconfig
@@ -305,6 +305,13 @@ config DEBUG_UART_APBUART
 	  will need to provide parameters to make this work. The driver will
 	  be available until the real driver model serial is running.
 
+config DEBUG_UART_LINFLEXUART
+	bool "Linflex UART"
+	select FSL_LINFLEXUART
+	help
+	  Select this to enable debug UART for Linflex module found on NXP
+	  Automotive SoCs like S32G/S32R.
+
 config DEBUG_UART_PL010
 	bool "pl010"
 	help
